back the measurements

00:14:19.640 --> 00:14:21.000
to the same space.

00:14:21.000 --> 00:14:22.777
So if you update your SDK--

00:14:22.777 --> 00:14:24.110
yeah, I think that's a cool one.

00:14:27.730 --> 00:14:29.980
So this keeps contact
registered to the environment

00:14:29.980 --> 00:14:32.260
even if the user walks away
or puts it in their pocket

00:14:32.260 --> 00:14:34.270
and brings it back
out, as long as it's

00:14:34.270 --> 00:14:36.710
within the same session.

00:14:36.710 --> 00:14:38.260
So if you update
the app and you work

00:14:38.260 --> 00:14:39.970
in one of the
current SDKs, you'll

00:14:39.970 --> 00:14:42.400
have this online drift
correction for you

00:14:42.400 --> 00:14:44.247
automatically.

