00:23:53.210 --> 00:23:56.070
So when you think of Lowe's,
you don't necessarily

00:23:56.070 --> 00:23:58.590
think of emerging
tech like Tango.

00:23:58.590 --> 00:24:00.930
Every organization
on the planet says

00:24:00.930 --> 00:24:03.540
they want to create the
new disruptive tools,

00:24:03.540 --> 00:24:05.277
but that's harder than it seems.

00:24:05.277 --> 00:24:07.110
There are two things
you have to figure out.

00:24:07.110 --> 00:24:11.700
What you want to work on, and
what you don't want to work on.

00:24:11.700 --> 00:24:13.200
So to figure that
out, we get people

00:24:13.200 --> 00:24:15.300
together inside and
outside of the company

00:24:15.300 --> 00:24:17.080
to work on those things.

00:24:17.080 --> 00:24:18.870
You need an intuitive
way, though,

00:24:18.870 --> 00:24:20.910
to be able to help people
understand the future.

00:24:20.910 --> 00:24:22.410
That's a hard thing.

00:24:22.410 --> 00:24:23.610
We do that through stories.

00:24:23.610 --> 00:24:26.220
So we create actual
narratives about the future

00:24:26.220 --> 00:24:27.720
we want to build,
and then we work

00:24:27.720 --> 00:24:29.640
backwards to bring it to life.

00:24:29.640 --> 00:24:32.160
This is a scene, actually,
from our first story

00:24:32.160 --> 00:24:33.932
that we turned
into a comic book,

00:24:33.932 --> 00:24:36.390
and it turned out to be the
most disruptive tool we've ever

00:24:36.390 --> 00:24:39.390
built. One of the hardest
things about home improvement

00:24:39.390 --> 00:24:43.890
is that it's really, really hard
to envision how your project is

00:24:43.890 --> 00:24:46.770
going to turn out, and
even harder to communicate

00:24:46.770 --> 00:24:50.580
that to the person
you have to convince;

00:24:50.580 --> 00:24:52.390
to communicate that
to somebody else.

00:24:52.390 --> 00:24:56.670
So it's estimated that about $70
billion in projects every year

00:24:56.670 --> 00:25:00.610
go unfulfilled, just because
of this visualization problem.

00:25:00.610 --> 00:25:02.730
So we knew that we could
use visualization tech

00:25:02.730 --> 00:25:05.890
to build new tools that could
help solve this problem.

00:25:05.890 --> 00:25:09.150
And we used the comic book to
show our executive team what

00:25:09.150 --> 00:25:10.350
the future would look like.

00:25:10.350 --> 00:25:12.720
And it's all about bringing
those intuitive solutions

00:25:12.720 --> 00:25:15.850
to life in order to
influence human behavior.

00:25:15.850 --> 00:25:18.810
It's not about building
tech for Tech's sake,

00:25:18.810 --> 00:25:21.060
and our executives'
reaction to the comic book,

00:25:21.060 --> 00:25:24.580
after seeing what we could
do, was to go build it.

00:25:24.580 --> 00:25:27.570
So we did it, and
four years ago, we

00:25:27.570 --> 00:25:32.130
brought the first iteration of
that augmented reality design

00:25:32.130 --> 00:25:34.470
solution that we call
the Holoroom, into two

00:25:34.470 --> 00:25:35.820
of our Canadian stores.

00:25:35.820 --> 00:25:38.430
So it was really
early-- four years ago--

00:25:38.430 --> 00:25:39.820
and the tech was rough.

00:25:39.820 --> 00:25:44.105
But we use our stores as
living labs that would show us,

00:25:44.105 --> 00:25:46.230
so we could get real feedback
from actual customers

00:25:46.230 --> 00:25:49.740
and employees, not just to
create solutions that work,

00:25:49.740 --> 00:25:52.380
but solutions that actually
work for real people

00:25:52.380 --> 00:25:54.240
and our customers.

00:25:54.240 --> 00:25:57.960
And we talked about what we
were doing really loudly,

00:25:57.960 --> 00:25:59.880
and the intention of
that is to attract

00:25:59.880 --> 00:26:03.010
more what we call uncommon
partners, the kinds of people

00:26:03.010 --> 00:26:04.760
and organizations that
you wouldn't expect

00:26:04.760 --> 00:26:06.930
a Lowe's to work
with, that could

00:26:06.930 --> 00:26:08.230
help us achieve this narrative.

00:26:08.230 --> 00:26:10.380
So Google was one of
our earliest partners

00:26:10.380 --> 00:26:11.590
to respond to that call.

00:26:11.590 --> 00:26:14.520
And from the earliest days
of exploring AR and VR,

00:26:14.520 --> 00:26:18.510
we worked with Google to push
the future further, faster.

00:26:18.510 --> 00:26:20.130
And in fact, in the
second generation,

00:26:20.130 --> 00:26:21.671
as you can see here,
of the Holoroom,

