for developers

00:30:58.100 --> 00:31:00.230
to map indoor environments,
and then create

00:31:00.230 --> 00:31:02.850
location based AR experiences.

00:31:02.850 --> 00:31:06.925
So let's get into the
details of how it works.

00:31:06.925 --> 00:31:08.300
The visual
positioning service is

00:31:08.300 --> 00:31:11.060
comprised of three components--
mapping, cloud processing,

00:31:11.060 --> 00:31:14.390
and client localization.

00:31:14.390 --> 00:31:17.870
The first step is that
of creating a map.

00:31:17.870 --> 00:31:20.420
So, in a venue
which has given us

00:31:20.420 --> 00:31:22.400
permission, such as
this Lowe's store,

00:31:22.400 --> 00:31:25.130
collection involves
walking through the store

00:31:25.130 --> 00:31:27.830
through the main pathways
with a Tango device.

00:31:27.830 --> 00:31:29.420
With a wide angle
camera, combined

00:31:29.420 --> 00:31:31.740
with the motion tracking
capabilities of the Tango

00:31:31.740 --> 00:31:34.350
Stack, it creates a data
set of the environment,

00:31:34.350 --> 00:31:36.230
which you can see on the right.

00:31:36.230 --> 00:31:38.000
When this collection
pass is completed,

00:31:38.000 --> 00:31:41.360
the data gets uploaded
into the cloud, which

00:31:41.360 --> 00:31:42.980
brings us to our second step--

00:31:42.980 --> 00:31:46.680
the cloud processing pipeline.

00:31:46.680 --> 00:31:49.950
So here's a visualization
of an aggregation

00:31:49.950 --> 00:31:53.060
of all the different mapping
runs for a given Lowe's store.

00:31:53.060 --> 00:31:56.070
In every frame, we're detecting
hundreds of visual features

00:31:56.070 --> 00:31:58.290
to compute the 3D location
of corresponding points

00:31:58.290 --> 00:31:59.310
in the scene.

00:31:59.310 --> 00:32:01.920
These collected data sets
are then processed, aligned,

00:32:01.920 --> 00:32:05.040
and compressed, using
middle-out, into a cloud map.

00:32:05.040 --> 00:32:08.910
This mapping is based on
purely visual feature tracking.

00:32:08.910 --> 00:32:10.100
It doesn't need Bluetooth.

00:32:10.100 --> 00:32:11.050
It doesn't need Wi-Fi.

00:32:11.050 --> 00:32:13.440
It doesn't need GPS
to create this map.

00:32:13.440 --> 00:32:15.930
And every capture and
recapture of a venue

00:32:15.930 --> 00:32:18.265
is incorporated to the
map and improves it.

00:32:18.265 --> 00:32:20.940
An important note here on size.

00:32:20.940 --> 00:32:23.460
One of our larger venues
that's currently running on VPS

00:32:23.460 --> 00:32:27.660
is a shopping mall, over
900,000 square feet.

00:32:27.660 --> 00:32:29.120
And in that shopping
mall, we use

00:32:29.120 --> 00:32:33.270
over 1.3 million key frames, 37
million landmarks, and over 300

00:32:33.270 --> 00:32:36.210
million key points to provide
localization of anywhere

00:32:36.210 --> 00:32:38.310
from a centimeter
to five centimeters.

00:32:38.310 --> 00:32:42.300
So this is a scalable system
to tackle not only your living

00:32:42.300 --> 00:32:47.810
room, but massive,
massive indoor facilities.

00:32:47.810 --> 00:32:51.260
Now, once VCS has completed
its cloud processing step,

00:32:51.260 --> 00:32:52.980
we now have a map
of the environment

00:32:52.980 --> 00:32:56.720
which any Tango enabled
device can localize against.

00:32:56.720 --> 00:33:01.926
So let's return to
that same Lowe's store.

