00:33:13.880 --> 00:33:15.890
To be able to
localize in a space,

00:33:15.890 --> 00:33:17.750
the user needs to give
the app permission

00:33:17.750 --> 00:33:21.290
to use both the camera
and location permissions.

00:33:21.290 --> 00:33:23.420
Once the user has granted
those permissions,

00:33:23.420 --> 00:33:24.920
as it moves through
the environment,

00:33:24.920 --> 00:33:27.920
it's looking for visual
features and matching those

00:33:27.920 --> 00:33:29.510
against the stored cloud map.

00:33:29.510 --> 00:33:32.360
This provides continuous
adjustment and alignment

00:33:32.360 --> 00:33:35.510
between the device's position
and all the AR content which

00:33:35.510 --> 00:33:36.995
has been placed in that space.

00:33:40.220 --> 00:33:56.090
So VPS provides you, the
developer, a coordinate system

00:33:56.090 --> 00:33:59.990
to overlay digital content
into the real world.

00:33:59.990 --> 00:34:03.800
